HEADWORD: Lithontriptic
<hw>Lith`on*trip"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>li`qos</grk>, acc. <?/, a stone + <?/ to rub, grind: cf. F.
<ets>lithontriptique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Having the
quality of, or used for, dissolving or destroying stone in the bladder
or kidneys; <as>as, <ex>lithontriptic</ex> forc⟦eacute⟧ps</as>.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A lithontriptic remedy or agent, as distilled
water.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

